    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Inspection - Valve Seat Leakage
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Valve Seat Leakage</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>This test does not check for the condition of the valve guides or the valve stem-to-valve guide
                    clearance.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the cylinder head on wood blocks with the gasket surface facing down.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Squirt mineral spirits into the intake and exhaust valve ports and wait 5 minutes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an inspection mirror to check valve seat area for leakage of the mineral spirits past
                the valve seats.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If leakage occurs, the valves must be reconditioned.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
